//! expected signature bytes generated from this implementation with a
//! fixed all-zero signing-key seed and a fixed message.  Any change in
//! the underlying `ml-dsa` crate that alters output will be caught here.
//!
//! Vector provenance: generated by running `SigningKey{44,65}::from_bytes(&[0u8;32])`
//! and signing the fixed message b"NIST FIPS 204 ML-DSA-65 KAT message", then
//! recording the exact byte output.  ML-DSA `try_sign` is deterministic (empty
//! context, no hedging randomness) so these vectors are stable across runs.
//!
